== Dough ==

Mix your @yeast{2%tsp} with @water{400%ml}(warm, not hot) and a @sugar{pinch}. Put @flour{600%g} in a big #mixing bowl{} and stir in @salt{1%tsp}. Make a well in the middle of the flour big enough to hold the yeast mixture. Tip the yeast mixture and @olive oil{1%tbsp} into the well.

Start bringing the flour in from the sides with your hands and mixing it with the liquid. Keep bringing the flour into the liquid and mixing everything until you have a nice squidgy ball of dough.

Sprinkle half your remaining @flour{100%g} on a dry work surface and place the dough on here. Knead it for ~{5%minutes} (at least).

> Kneading simply means stretching the dough to make it nice and springy. Hold
> down the end of the dough nearest to you with your hand and use the palm of
> the other hand to push the rest of the dough away from you in a long stretching
> motion, fold it in half and repeat... you're now kneading!

Once the dough is ready, leave it in a #bowl{} in a warm place for at least ~{15%minutes} to prove.

> For best results, you can leave it a little longer!

== Vegetables ==

Meanwhile, pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{2} and chop into 3cm chunks. Chop the base from the @leek{1} then slice it in half lengthways. Slice it thinly into half moon shapes. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{2} in half.

Put your chopped veggies on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over @olive oil{3%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{}. Pop them in the oven to cook for ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through. At the same time, pop a large piece of #tin foil{} on two #baking trays{}, lightly oil them and put them in the oven, ready for the pizza bases.

== Chorizo ==

Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and once hot add the @chorizo{2%diced}. Cook for a few mins until ever so slightly crispy at the edges, then take the pan off the heat.

== Pizza Assembly ==

When the pizza dough is ready, dust the work surface with the remaining flour, divide your dough into two balls and roll them out on the floured surface until nice and thin - roughly 25cm across.

> If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle.

Spread @tomato puree{8%tbsp} thinly over each pizza base.

Once the veggies are soft and sweet, take them out of the oven and divide them between each pizza base. Turn your oven to 220 degrees. Tear the @mozzarella{2} on top of the vegetables and sprinkle over the @Italian style herbs{1} and chorizo.

> To prevent the pizza base getting soggy, be careful not to add any excess water
> from the vegetables.

Pop both pizzas on top of the lightly oiled pre-heated baking trays, on the top
shelf of the oven for ~{8-10%minutes}. Job done!